            <h5>WHAT ARE THE SYMPTOMS OF COVID-19?</h5>
            <h3>SYMPTOMS OF CORONAVIRUS</h3>
            <p>
                The most common symptoms of COVID-19 are fever, tiredness, and dry cough.
                Some patients may<br> have aches and pains, nasal congestion, runny nose, sore throat or diarrhea.
                These symptoms are <br>usually mild and begin gradually. Also the symptoms may appear 2-14 days after
                exposure.
            </p>
